    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email. We had a candidate, Marcus, who made it all the way to the final interview for our Senior Dev role here in Austin. He's really talented and had great technical skills, but we decided to go with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. I want the email to be professional and kind because he was a great guy, but we need to be firm that the decision is final. Can you draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Dev Role\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to take a moment to thank you for your interest in the Senior Dev role at our Austin-based company. We were genuinely impressed by your technical skills and the enthusiasm you brought to the interview process. Your talent and potential are evident, and we appreciate the time you invested in sharing your journey with us.\n\nAfter careful consideration, we have decided to move forward with another candidate who has a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. This decision was not easy, as we were very impressed with your abilities and the unique perspective you could bring to our team. However, we believe that this particular candidate's experience aligns more closely with our current needs.\n\nWe understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that this decision was not a reflection of your skills or potential. We genuinely wish you the best in your future endeavors and hope that you will keep an eye on our career page for future opportunities that may be a better fit.\n\nThank you once again for considering us as a potential employer. We wish you all the best in your career and hope that you will continue to pursue your passion for technology.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your",
