      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks, that's a good start. It's a bit formal, though. Can we make it feel a little less \"corporate robot\" and maybe add a line or two that acknowledges how tough the competitive landscape is right now for devs, just to make it feel a bit more human and empathetic? Not too mushy, just more sincere.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for the Senior Dev Role\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI hope this message finds you well. I wanted to take a moment to thank you for your interest in the Senior Dev role at our Austin-based company. We were genuinely impressed by your technical skills and the enthusiasm you brought to the interview process. Your talent and potential are evident, and we appreciate the time you invested in sharing your journey with us.\n\nIn the ever-evolving landscape of development, it's tough to find the right fit, especially when the competition is fierce. We understand that this news may be disappointing, and we want to assure you that this decision was not a reflection of your skills or potential. We genuinely wish you the best in your future endeavors and hope that you will keep an eye on our career page for future opportunities that may be a better fit.\n\nWe understand that this decision was not easy, and we want to acknowledge the hard work and dedication you put into your application. We wish you all the best in your career and hope that you continue to pursue your passion for technology.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]",
